    en: "The Town of Brighton requires a plumber to register with the town before pulling a plumbing permit. A plumber holding a City of Rochester Examining Board of Plumbers certificate can use that credential to qualify for a Brighton license. A homeowner can do their own plumbing work in a single-family home they own and occupy, with a permit and inspection. Fixture-based fees apply. Town Code chapter 215 (Plumbers, Licensing of) governs the licensing rules."
